@olafurpg What about declarations? For example if we have somewhere defined

```
trait T { 
  type X
  val x: X 
}
```

`X` will be a `Decl.Type` and `x` a `Decl.Val`, so if later in the code we encounter something like `def foo(t: T): t.X` and want to lookup that `t.X`... No, this example is bad, but I think you got the idea. If not, I'll think of a better example, sorry ðŸ˜…
